The paper discusses the use of Software Defined Networking (SDN) to improve the performance of inter-domain routing, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the shortcomings of the Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) and proposes a probabilistic framework to analyze the effects of centralization on inter-domain routing performance, which are topics related to cryptography and security (cs.CR), systems and control (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
